# Subsystem Documentation Rules

Guidelines for creating and maintaining subsystem documentation.

---

## Folder Structure

Every subsystem folder should contain:

```
subsystem-name/
├── README.md           # Required: Overview and entry point
├── open-points.md      # Required: Track unresolved questions
├── component-a.md      # Detailed component documentation
├── component-b.md      # Additional components as needed
└── diagrams/           # Optional: Complex diagram assets
```

---

## README.md Requirements

Every subsystem README must include:

### Required Sections

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Overview** | 2-3 sentence description of subsystem purpose |
| **Architecture** | Diagram showing high-level structure |
| **Key Concepts** | Table defining core terms/entities |
| **Components** | List with links to detailed docs |
| **Core Responsibilities** | What this subsystem does |
| **Integration Points** | Inbound and outbound connections |

### Optional Sections

| Section | When to Include |
|---------|-----------------|
| **Configuration** | If subsystem has configurable settings |
| **Security** | If subsystem handles sensitive data/operations |
| **Performance** | If subsystem has SLA or scaling considerations |

### Quality Checklist

Before finalizing a subsystem README:

- [ ] Overview is concise (2-3 sentences max)
- [ ] Architecture diagram is present and readable
- [ ] All key concepts are defined
- [ ] All components have links to detailed docs
- [ ] Responsibilities are clear and bounded
- [ ] Non-responsibilities are stated (clarifies scope)
- [ ] Integration points list source/target and interface type
- [ ] Related documentation links are valid
- [ ] Open points file is linked

---

## Component Documentation Requirements

For each component within a subsystem:

### Required Sections

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Overview** | What this component does |
| **Role in Parent** | How it fits in the subsystem |
| **Responsibilities** | What it handles |
| **Non-Responsibilities** | Explicit boundaries |
| **Data Model** | Key entities with schemas |
| **Behavior** | Operations and flows |

### Optional Sections

| Section | When to Include |
|---------|-----------------|
| **Interfaces** | If component exposes API/contracts |
| **Events** | If component emits/consumes events |
| **Configuration** | If component is configurable |
| **Error Handling** | If error scenarios are non-obvious |
| **Examples** | Always helpful; include when possible |

---

## Diagrams

### When to Use Diagrams

- **Architecture overview** — Always in README
- **Complex flows** — When >3 steps or multiple actors
- **Data relationships** — Entity relationships, state machines
- **Integration patterns** — How subsystem connects to others

### Diagram Standards

#### ASCII Art (Simple Diagrams)

```
┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐
│ Component A │────▶│ Component B │
└─────────────┘     └─────────────┘
```

#### Mermaid (Complex Diagrams)

````markdown
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Component A] --> B[Component B]
    B --> C[Component C]
```
````

### Diagram Maintenance

- Update diagrams when architecture changes
- Date diagrams if they may become stale
- Reference diagrams from text; don't rely on diagrams alone

---

## Cross-References

### Linking Patterns

| Link Type | Format |
|-----------|--------|
| **Same folder** | `[Component](component.md)` |
| **Parent folder** | `[Parent](../README.md)` |
| **Sibling subsystem** | `[Other](../other-subsystem/README.md)` |
| **ADR** | `[ADR-0001](../../decision-logs/0001-decision.md)` |
| **Guide** | `[Guide](../../10-guides/guide-name.md)` |

### Required Cross-References

Every subsystem document should link to:

- [ ] Parent subsystem README (for components)
- [ ] Related ADRs (for decisions made)
- [ ] Related guides (for how-to content)
- [ ] Related subsystems (for dependencies)

---

## Open Points Management

### When to Add Open Points

- Unresolved design questions
- Pending decisions needing stakeholder input
- Deferred items with clear deferral reason
- Assumptions that need validation

### Open Points Lifecycle

```
Question arises → Document in open-points.md
       │
       ▼
Discussion/Decision → Create ADR if significant
       │
       ▼
Update open-points.md → Move to "Resolved" section
```

### Open Points Review

- Review weekly during active development
- Clear "Resolved" items that are >1 month old
- Escalate "Under Discussion" items stale >2 weeks

---

## Consistency Standards

### Terminology

- Use glossary terms consistently
- Define new terms in Key Concepts table
- Add new terms to glossary

### Formatting

- Use tables for structured data
- Use bullet lists for related items
- Use numbered lists for sequences
- Use code blocks for schemas/examples

### Tone

- Be direct and specific
- Avoid hedging language ("might", "could", "possibly")
- State assumptions explicitly
- Distinguish facts from recommendations

---

## Review Checklist

Before merging subsystem documentation:

### Structure
- [ ] Follows folder structure
- [ ] README has all required sections
- [ ] Components have required sections
- [ ] Open points file exists

### Content
- [ ] Overview is accurate and concise
- [ ] Diagrams are present and accurate
- [ ] Key concepts are defined
- [ ] Responsibilities are clear
- [ ] Boundaries are explicit

### Quality
- [ ] Cross-references are valid
- [ ] Terminology is consistent
- [ ] Examples are included
- [ ] ADRs exist for significant decisions

### Integration
- [ ] Added to parent index
- [ ] Related subsystems updated if needed
- [ ] Glossary updated if new terms
